From Damian Duruiheoma, Owerri  A police inspector attached to Imo State government house, Owerri was on Tuesday found dead along Avana Primary School Road, Shell Camp in Owerri, the state capital. According to police sources, the inspector, Haruna Kawura’s death was not natural as, according to him, the deceased was strangulated to death. Our correspondent learned that the lifeless body of the inspector was riddled with bruises raising suspicion that he was killed. The inspector was said to have gone out for drinks on Monday night and only to be found lying dead on Tuesday morning. When our correspondent visited the scene, people including policemen were seen discussing his death and what could have led to his death. A colleague of the deceased told our correspondent that the corpse of the inspector was evacuated in an ambulance from the government house. He said “The victim is Haruna Kawura. He was an inspector of police. He was demobbed from mobile police in the North and was posted to Imo state and was later posted to Imo government house. “His death was strange. There were bruises on his body. He must have been strangulated as there was gunshot on his body.” When contacted, the police spokesperson in the state, Orlando Ikeokwu, confirmed the killing and disclosed that investigation had commenced on the matter.